stories.title: Twenty20 reasons to be cheerful
stories.summary:
Marcus Trescothick: a very un-English innings     
 
 
 The man at the ECB who thought up the Twenty20 Cup can give
himself a pat on the back of his blazer today
stories.byline: The Wisden Verdict by Steven Lynch

stories.title: Anderson and Trescothick batter Pakistan to defeat
stories.summary:
James Anderson: a wicket with his first ball, and then wrapped things up with a hat-trick    
 
 
 Experience is the key, so the sages say, if England's young side are to compete with the best by the 2007 World Cup
stories.byline: The Wisden Bulletin by Andrew Miller
